        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>SUBSECTION 2.  WARRANTY OF PEACEFUL POSSESSION
Art. 2700.  Warranty of peaceful possession
The lessor warrants the lessee's peaceful possession of the leased thing against any disturbance caused by a person who asserts ownership, or right to possession of, or any other right in the thing.
In a residential lease, this warranty encompasses a disturbance caused by a person who, with the lessor's consent, has access to the thing or occupies adjacent property belonging to the lessor.</p>
        </content>
